        <ol start="2" style="margin-top: 0;">
         <li style="margin-bottom: 3.75px; margin-left: 7.5px; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 3.75px;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">
           He took a \xe2\x80\x9c12 month break\xe2\x80\x9d to follow his wave of friends going into consulting.
          </p>
         </li>
        </ol>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         For his \xe2\x80\x9cgap year,\xe2\x80\x9d Matt joined McKinsey to see the world, travel around, and work in healthcare from the business side. By year two, he deferred residency again and started doing non-medical consulting work. By year three, when McKinsey sent him to the US to work on tech and education clients, he realized that he was never going to go back to being a doctor.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Instead, he refocused on GownTown, and realized, both thinking like a consultant and remembering his mom\xe2\x80\x99s graduation emotions, that there was an even bigger adjacent opportunity: graduation
         <em>
          photography
         </em>
         .
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Snappr was born.
        </p>
        <h3 style="-moz-osx-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; color: #1a1a1a; font-family: 'SF Compact Display', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 1.375em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.16em; margin: 1em 0 0.625em 0;">
         <strong>
          Was the Picture Clear from the Start?
         </strong>
        </h3>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Let\xe2\x80\x99s pause here for a second.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Whenever I see a strategy that looks brilliantly constructed, I try to figure out whether it was all part of the plan from the beginning. Sometimes, companies go to great lengths to tell a coherent narrative that makes the company\xe2\x80\x99s history look like the unfolding of a masterfully orchestrated master plan. That\xe2\x80\x99s rarely the case.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         In Snappr\xe2\x80\x99s case, all of the ingredients were there for a smart consultant to piece together.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         There was the
         <strong>
          market trend
         </strong>
         . Digital photos were becoming a bigger part of both consumers\xe2\x80\x99 and businesses\xe2\x80\x99 identities. The internet had become more visual. Airbnb was a
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxNkcuO5CAMRb-m2BHxSk2yyKI3_RuRASegTgDx6Ch_P1TVYkayQNiYa841UHGP-V5SLJW8lrXeCZeAVzmwVsykFcyrtwt_ikmOaiZ2UZZP40R8WbeMeII_lpobktT04Q1UH8O7gzExErfMzMD2Z36iNRpQKQEjcMX1bOXEZ2E-utCsx2BwwV_MdwxIjsXVmspDfj3Ed4_ruoYSIKU8mHj2BIY-YMq-INVH3HsmuVjjniG5m1YHlR7QgnFoKQSKZ_IZqYsXBZ910LRmCGWL-ewXqkOfqW7FByyFXr46mnLc-qH_Bw7639vEL4KJHpxxOUopBzEwPaoNQW98niZj9YDb3cA-20OxcxdDabpUMD-v2UleQqw6Zh_2Xv5xcOLxLnSEa9_PFny9VwygD7QfuvVj0pv3umPA3M2zK9RujVIj40LwmcsPzY5fTSNjUirSlW3sXeGf6F_qE7DT" rel="" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          case study
         </a>
         for the value of high-quality photography. People and businesses alike would need, and be willing to pay for, higher-quality photos.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Then there was the
         <strong>
          market structure
         </strong>
         . I didn\xe2\x80\x99t know this until Matt told me, but there was only one services industry more fragmented pre-marketplaces than the photography industry: taxis. Putting a digital marketplace on top of that industry resulted in multiple multi-deca-billion dollar companies, including Uber, Lyft, and Didi.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Unlike those companies, though, who would need to await the arrival of self-driving cars to produce software margins, the margin expansion opportunities for photography were manifold, from editing to storage to asset management to distribution.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         You\xe2\x80\x99d just need to grab the consumer market as a wedge, build up liquidity, write some code, sell the whole package to enterprises, and Bob\xe2\x80\x99s your uncle.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Well, I got to ask Matt directly whether the plan all along was to go from B2C to B2B to SaaS and infrastructure.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         The answer was a resounding, Australian-accented \xe2\x80\x9cno.\xe2\x80\x9d (noyr?)
        </p>
        <a class="youtube-wrap" href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkMtqxDAMRb8mXga_MnUWXhTKlEK_YDbBDyVjJrGDI0_I39czWRQuEkhcXXScQZhSPvSaNiSvMuCxgo6wbzMgQiZlgzwEr9mFK9HJnngtPVOdImEbxgywmDBrzAXIWuwcnMGQ4ttBKe_IXTtqvVVK9eyDfYyU9kwIyTsjjPdCUH_mmuIDRAcanpCPFIHM-o64bo34bPi1at_39kgFi4XWpeU1Mejujbg-G_H1fZt-1fDjbuLR8MuGJmOdcrWRoDnlVYwy0QkhWt5S28kRjB1Zr5TztoXxKMZfSiPpMvF2K7ZecI9XDsk6JrQphzjV9eNuFpjfi_rvUPtSYsBjgGjsDP5EgSfRN5xhggi5kvaDwcpRyo4yzlnlcL5eWUnVUVqxkJrsU3XF_9A_KpKM2A" rel="" style="display: block; margin: 1.6em 0;" target="_blank">
         <img src="https://cdn.substack.com/image/youtube/w_550,c_limit/l_youtube_play_qyqt8q,w_120/GZgL8_IcZ3k" style="-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic; border: none !important; display: block; height: auto; margin: 0 auto; max-width: 100%; vertical-align: middle; width: 100%;"/>
        </a>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Through his experience running GownTown, Matt just saw that there might be an opportunity to build a marketplace for graduation photographers. Then, McKinsey moved him to the US, and when he got here, he said that he\xc2\xa0 started thinking bigger. Instead of just graduation photography, Snappr wanted to make it easy to book any professional photographer on-demand. They applied and got into Y Combinator.
        </p>
